	<LINE>THE Corporation grant Drafts, and negotiate or collect Bills, payable at the above places,</LINE>
	<LINE>on terms which may be ascertained at their OiEce ; they also issue Circular Notes and</LINE>
	<LINE>Letters of Credit negotiable in most parts of the World.</LINE>
	<LINE>They undertake the Agency of Persons connected with India and the Colonies, make</LINE>
	<LINE>investments in the Public Funds, and other British and Foreign Securities, and receive Pay,</LINE>
	<LINE>Pension, Dividends, and Interest for Constituents.</LINE>
	<LINE>They also receive Deposits for fixed periods, repayable in one sum, on terms which can</LINE>
	<LINE>be ascertained at their Ofiice.</LINE>
	<LINE>Applications for the sanction of the Directors to Credits established by Firms here in</LINE>
	<LINE>favour of parties abroad should be sent in not less than three days before despatch of the Mail,</LINE>
	<LINE>otherwise they might be deferred until the Mail following. Bills for Collection in India and</LINE>
	<LINE>the Colonies, and other transactions involving correspondence by Outward Mails, also applica-</LINE>
	<LINE>tion for Drafts, should be sent in one clear day before the day of despatch.</LINE>
	<LINE>The Corporation undertake the custody of Indian and Colonial Government Paper,</LINE>
	<LINE>Bank Shares, and other Stocks, and draw Interest and Dividends on the same as they fall</LINE>
	<LINE>due.</LINE>
	<LINE>They also make the necessary Registry of Indian Government Loan Notes, so as to</LINE>
	<LINE>obtain payment of the Interest in England.</LINE>
	<LINE>The Corporation have Correspondents in Western Australia, South Australia,</LINE>
	<LINE>Queensland, Tasmania, New Zealand, California, Canada, The United States of</LINE>
	<LINE>America, South America, South Africa, and in the principal Cities of the Continent of</LINE>
